# Diet Tracker — Core

## Before coding

1. Read `memory-bank/activeContext.md` and `memory-bank/progress.md`.
2. For feature work, cross-check `PRD.md` and the relevant memory-bank file.
3. Update `memory-bank/progress.md` when completing a build-plan milestone.

## Non-negotiables

- **Single user** — Firebase Auth; Firestore rules `request.auth.uid == uid`.
- **English UI (LTR)** — Hebrew only in meal text inputs/display via `dir="auto"` / `lang="he"`.
- **Dates** — Persist `YYYY-MM-DD` in **Asia/Jerusalem**; compute on server for writes, not client `Date` for boundaries.
- **Secrets** — `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` only in Route Handlers; never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
- **v1 scope** — Calories only; no macros, social, exercise, native apps.

## Architecture

- Client → Firestore for CRUD; server route **only** for `/api/estimate`.
- Real-time Firestore listeners on today view; optimistic meal rows while estimating.

## Quality bar

- Mobile-first; test iPhone Safari gestures (swipe days).
- Zod-validate LLM JSON before Firestore writes.
- Minimal diff; match existing patterns once scaffold exists.
